@startuml
title 02. Package Policy (Python target implementation baseline)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

package "src/app" {
  package "api" {
    [agent endpoints]
    [a2a endpoints]
    [support]
  }
  package "application" {
    [agent]
    [prompt]
  }
  package "domain" {
    [agent]
  }
  package "infrastructure" {
    [mcp]
    [redis]
    [settings]
    [llm]
  }
  package "a2a" {
    [dto]
    [mapper]
    [task]
    [lifecycle]
  }
}

note bottom
Package rules
- endpoint -> application -> domain -> infrastructure
- internal naming uses snake_case
- store/gateway/client/adapter names are preferred over repository
- compatibility layer may preserve external A2A aliases only
end note

@enduml
